<plot>Hosted by Abe Burrows, who was billed as "The bald-headed baritone from Brooklyn," and would go on to gain greater fame as a writer of Broadway musicals. This show followed a fairly casual format, with the easy-going Burrows inviting celebrities from music and film to come and talk about their lives and current projects.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?021031</url></doc>
